<br>
As for the hoses, I can get you silicone heater hoses.  Tell me what's the inside diameter of these hoses, and I can get them for you.  However, we do not carry &quot;pre-formed&quot; hoses found on some of the merkur lines.  I got some hoses for heater hoses at this address:  http://www.hoseline.net/ahe/ahh.htm<br>
<br>
We can bend tubes.  Ship them to us, we can probably help you.  Give us the length of the tube; give us the number of bends, and outside diameter (inches) of the tubing.  It takes us one to two days to copy the tubing lines.<br>
<br>
However, I also suggest you go to your local welder for this job; this is probably the cheapest way.  This is quite simple for them to repair.  I suspect you have a crack on this tube line.  A simple brazing weld will patch most cracks and punctures.<br>
<br>
I just looked at my Merkur XR4Ti 1986 automatic, and it looks like it has a couple of bends and branches.  I have never had any problems with the tube itself, but I have had a problem with the hoses, which I have replaced 3 years or so ago.  I don't remember exactly, but that's when I think I did it.<br>
